## Syntax and Formatting

## Code Style
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use proper JSDoc comments
- Maintain clean code structure

## Audio Parameters
- Format bitrates with 'k' suffix
- Use numeric literals for sample rates
- Format metadata as key-value pairs
- Use consistent parameter ordering

## FFmpeg Commands
- One argument per line for complex commands
- Group related arguments together
- Include comments for complex operations
- Use consistent flag ordering

## Error Messages
- Use consistent error message format
- Include relevant parameter values
- Format stack traces consistently
- Use proper error types

## Documentation
- Use consistent markdown formatting
- Format code examples properly
- Use proper heading hierarchy
- Include proper code blocks

## Comments
- Document complex audio processing
- Explain FFmpeg argument choices
- Note performance considerations
- Document format-specific behavior
